As I see it the fourth parameter to the `sms.sendTextMessage("1990", null, s, pi, null)` function, the `pi` PendingIntent, will start your smsShower Activity after the message has been sent.

What I don't see is where the Intent that is caught in your broadcast receiver comes from? Can't you parse the "pdus" from the Intent directly in the smsShower onCreate() instead? (especially as the `pi` PendingIntent starts the Activity rather than triggers the BroadcastReceiver as it is stated in your code).

Also I have a bad feeling for the way you get a reference to your smsShower Activity in the `onReceive()` function. You create a new `smsShower` on the second line within the function but that is no guarantee that it's the same Activity that was previously started. It's actually more or less a guarantee that it's not the same Activity.

